{
  "stem": "16887.3",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 37.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That was in the early spring of '46.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "When the-- when the transit came and it stopped in each place in Poland, there was thousands of people at the stations, because everybody was looking for somebody that came from Russia or survived.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So we came to a little town that used to be a taken by the-- the Germans used to-- they used to call them the false Deutsche used to live there.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 37,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And it was called Reichenbach.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, that's when.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They would change it later to Dzierzoniow.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So when the train stopped there, because we had no idea where they're taking us, when the train stopped and opened the door from the wagons, my husband saw, you know, his friends that he lived with in when he would race with him, grew up with him together.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "When they saw us, they ran into-- they jumped into the wagon, took-- took the kids, and took the few, you know, schmattas that we had, and said, you come and live with us.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They already had a-- a room.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Up till they had like a room and a little kitchen because they-- they evacuated the-- the Russians evacuated all the Germans, and they gave us their homes.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Probably, a couple months later.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was by sheer coincidence, because one of my husband's friends went back home where he lived, because my husband's brother returned from Russia on-- from Arkhangelsk, which is close by the Chinese border.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he found out my husband has another brother that lived in, at that time, in New York.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he found out that he send him money.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And he send money to share with anyone from the family that survived.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
